Okay, I suppose I can see why it wasn't released back then in Season 2, and it's certainly not their best rap battle, but I will admit it got a few chuckles out of me, particularly from the Bill's Saxaphone line. XD Congrats on the upcoming baby boy, NicePeter! :D Best of luck to you and EpicLloyd on creating more awesome raps!

Also, here's some suggestions for potential future raps while I'm thinking about it (I have commented a few of them before on another video I think, but might as well put them out here again, you never know if they'll be noticed. :'3):
Daryl Dixon (The Walking Dead) vs Burt Gummer (Tremors movies) (badass survivor vs badass survivalist?)
Benedict Arnold vs Judas (traitor vs traitor)
Rick Grimes vs Walter White 2 (Am I the only one who feels these two could have a lot more to say to each other? Maybe use a version of Rick further on into the show, more hardened and ruthless?)
Tony and Maria (West Side Story) vs Jack and Rose (Titanic) (couple vs couple where only one person in each couple survives)
